<TITLE> 48 children to spend Eid with mothers in central jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 20 (bdnews24.com) - Forty-eight children of women prisoners will spend Eid with their mothers at the Dhaka Central Jail. Women prisoners with children are allowed to look after them in prison, but there are no child prisoners in the central jail, say officials. "There are no child prisoners in the the central jail. All children and there are with their mothers," senior superintendent Mohammad Touhidul Islam told bdnews24.com. Jail authorities have made special arrangements for the children that include new clothes, special food, entertainment and games like chess, ludo and carom. "New clothes have been bought with money from the poor fund," said Islam. Sarees were bought for the mothers, too, he said. bdnew
